1. We can't know things for sure.
2. What we claim to know, at the very bottom, is held in faith.
3. To have faith is a choice.
4. What we choose to have faith in is based on arbitrary "anchors" such as aesthetic value, historical contingency, emotion, and other preferences.
    4.1 Beliefs reflect the preferences of those that believe.
5. As preferences are arbitrary, all preferences CAN be understood, accepted, and respected.
6. Understanding, acceptance, and respect towards whichever particular preference and point of view is a choice everyone can make.
